Öffne Classifier auf Windows\r\n2. Klicke auf Menü \"Einstellungen\"\r\n3. Klicke auf \"Konfigurationsordner öffnen\"\r\n4. Fehler: Es passiert nichts!\r\n\r\n**Erwartetes Verhalten**\r\nExplorer sollte den Pfad %LOCALAPPDATA%\\Classifier öffnen\r\n\r\n**Screenshots**\r\nFalls möglich, ist es hilfreich Screenshots des Fehlers hinzuzufügen.\r\n\r\n**Systeminformationen:**\r\n - OS: Windows 10\r\n\r\n**Zusätzliche Informationen**\r\nHier ist Platz für zusätzliche Informationen.\r\n\r\n**Logging**\r\nFalls möglich kann eine Log-Datei hinzugefügt werden. {"id":1239415876,"created_at":"2022-05-18T04:32:13Z","updated_at":"2022-05-22T14:28:22Z","state":"closed","title":"Fix right clicking a group and choosing \"remove selected entries from this group\" leads to error when Bibtex source tab is selected","html_url":"https://github.com/JabRef/jabref/pull/8821","body":"## Previous discussion about right clicking a group and choosing \"remove selected entries from this group\" leads to error when Bibtex source tab is selected #8012\r\nBig thank you to @ThiloteE and @Siedlerchr for all the provided information in #8012 that help me to find the root of this issue.\r\n\r\n## Root of issue #8012\r\n1. We have a entry with only `author` and `groups` as fields.\r\n![111](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49628911/168956444-1c3097c1-0edd-49db-9e20-a003241ab219.png)\r\n2. When we right click on group `111` and click on \"Remove selected entries from this group\", this entry will be deleted and still stay in `previousEntry` and `outOfFocusBound` variables.\r\n3. However, `previousEntry` or `outOfFocusBound` only have `author` as field after \"Remove selected entries from this group\".\r\n![111](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49628911/168956728-cfb198d2-90f5-4255-a622-6535aa12f3a0.png)\r\n4. In the image below, we are iterating through all fields in `newEntry` which has keys `author` and `groups`.\r\n![222](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49628911/168957351-55eb1c8d-f4d4-4331-84a1-cd3e40e5e94f.png)\r\n6. Since `outOfFocusBound` does not have `groups` field, assigning value to a null result in error.\r\n![222](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49628911/168957457-4b1c0c91-d634-4ba0-98c6-12e927779d56.png)\r\n\r\n## Proposed solution\r\nFixes #8012\r\nAdd a validation before setting value to a field.\r\n```\r\nif (outOfFocusEntry.getField(fieldName).isPresent()) {\r\n            outOfFocusEntry.setField(fieldName, newValue);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n<!-- \r\n- Go through the list below. Please don't remove any items.\r\n- [x] done; [ ] not done / not applicable\r\n-->\r\n\r\n- [ ] Change in `CHANGELOG.md` described in a way that is understandable for the average user (if applicable)\r\n- [ ] Tests created for changes (if applicable)\r\n- [x] Manually tested changed features in running JabRef (always required)\r\n- [x] Screenshots added in PR description (for UI changes)\r\n- [ ] [Checked developer's documentation](https://devdocs.jabref.org/): Is the information available and up to date? {"id":1234817545,"created_at":"2022-05-13T06:55:20Z","updated_at":"2022-05-15T13:44:53Z","state":"closed","title":"Add log on disk","html_url":"https://github.com/JabRef/jabref/pull/8791","body":"JabRef has a build-in logging framework. Howver, the log is hard to find and to open after JabRef has closed.\r\n\r\nThis PR adds logging to `%APPDATA%` using [AppDirs](https://github.com/harawata/appdirs).\r\n\r\nThe log is a rolling log and also configured for parallel writing (in case there are multiple local instances of JabRef - who knows...)\r\n\r\nExample:\r\n\r\n![grafik](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1366654/168227886-88c77821-0b3c-43e7-a19b-3ec721e5d657.png)\r\n\r\nContent:\r\n\r\n```\r\n2022-05-13 08:50:57 [JavaFX Application Thread] org.jabref.logic.net.ssl.TrustStoreManager.createTruststoreFileIfNotExist()\r\nINFO: Trust store path: C:\\Users\\koppor\\AppData\\Local\\org.jabref\\ssl\\truststore.jks\r\n2022-05-13 08:50:57 [JavaFX Application Thread] org.jabref.gui.JabRefMain.clearOldSearchIndices()\r\nINFO: Deleting out-of-date fulltext search index at C:\\Users\\koppor\\AppData\\Local\\org.jabref\\JabRef\\Cache.\r\n2022-05-13 08:50:57 [JavaFX Application Thread] org.jabref.gui.JabRefMain.clearOldSearchIndices()\r\nINFO: Deleting out-of-date fulltext search index at C:\\Users\\koppor\\AppData\\Local\\org.jabref\\JabRef\\Logs.\r\n2022-05-13 08:50:57 [JavaFX Application Thread] org.jabref.gui.theme.ThemeManager.addStylesheetToWatchlist()\r\nINFO: Watching css C:\\git-repositories\\jabref\\jabref\\build\\resources\\main\\org\\jabref\\gui\\Base.css for live updates\r\n2022-05-13 08:50:57 [JavaFX Application Thread] org.jabref.gui.theme.ThemeManager.updateThemeSettings()\r\nINFO: Not updating theme because it hasn't changed\r\n2022-05-13 08:50:57 [JavaFX Application Thread] org.jabref.gui.theme.ThemeManager.updateThemeSettings()\r\nINFO: Theme set to Theme{type=DEFAULT, name=''} with base css StyleSheet{file:/C:/git-repositories/jabref/jabref/build/resources/main/org/jabref/gui/Base.css}\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n- [x] Change in `CHANGELOG.md` described in a way that is understandable for the average user (if applicable)\r\n- [ ] Tests created for changes (if applicable)\r\n- [x] Manually tested changed features in running JabRef (always required)\r\n- [ ] Screenshots added in PR description (for UI changes)\r\n- [ ] [Checked developer's documentation](https://devdocs.jabref.org/): Is the information available and up to date? {"id":1239415876,"created_at":"2022-05-18T04:32:13Z","updated_at":"2022-05-22T14:28:22Z","state":"closed","title":"Fix right clicking a group and choosing \"remove selected entries from this group\" leads to error when Bibtex source tab is selected","html_url":"https://github.com/JabRef/jabref/pull/8821","body":"## Previous discussion about right clicking a group and choosing \"remove selected entries from this group\" leads to error when Bibtex source tab is selected #8012\r\nBig thank you to @ThiloteE and @Siedlerchr for all the provided information in #8012 that help me to find the root of this issue.\r\n\r\n## Root of issue #8012\r\n1. We have a entry with only `author` and `groups` as fields.\r\n![111](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49628911/168956444-1c3097c1-0edd-49db-9e20-a003241ab219.png)\r\n2. When we right click on group `111` and click on \"Remove selected entries from this group\", this entry will be deleted and still stay in `previousEntry` and `outOfFocusBound` variables.\r\n3. However, `previousEntry` or `outOfFocusBound` only have `author` as field after \"Remove selected entries from this group\".\r\n![111](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49628911/168956728-cfb198d2-90f5-4255-a622-6535aa12f3a0.png)\r\n4. In the image below, we are iterating through all fields in `newEntry` which has keys `author` and `groups`.\r\n![222](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49628911/168957351-55eb1c8d-f4d4-4331-84a1-cd3e40e5e94f.png)\r\n6. Since `outOfFocusBound` does not have `groups` field, assigning value to a null result in error.\r\n![222](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49628911/168957457-4b1c0c91-d634-4ba0-98c6-12e927779d56.png)\r\n\r\n## Proposed solution\r\nFixes #8012\r\nAdd a validation before setting value to a field.\r\n```\r\nif (outOfFocusEntry.getField(fieldName).isPresent()) {\r\n            outOfFocusEntry.setField(fieldName, newValue);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n<!-- \r\n- Go through the list below. Please don't remove any items.\r\n- [x] done; [ ] not done / not applicable\r\n-->\r\n\r\n- [ ] Change in `CHANGELOG.md` described in a way that is understandable for the average user (if applicable)\r\n- [ ] Tests created for changes (if applicable)\r\n- [x] Manually tested changed features in running JabRef (always required)\r\n- [x] Screenshots added in PR description (for UI changes)\r\n- [ ] [Checked developer's documentation](https://devdocs.jabref.org/): Is the information available and up to date? {"id":1234817545,"created_at":"2022-05-13T06:55:20Z","updated_at":"2022-05-15T13:44:53Z","state":"closed","title":"Add log on disk","html_url":"https://github.com/JabRef/jabref/pull/8791","body":"JabRef has a build-in logging framework. Howver, the log is hard to find and to open after JabRef has closed.\r\n\r\nThis PR adds logging to `%APPDATA%` using [AppDirs](https://github.com/harawata/appdirs).\r\n\r\nThe log is a rolling log and also configured for parallel writing (in case there are multiple local instances of JabRef - On [my repo](https://github.com/pauljackals/milkman) there's a release with this plugin's `jar`.\r\n\r\nRight now it supports:\r\n- connecting to namespaces\r\n- changing Socket.IO path\r\n- providing headers for initial request, like `Cookie`\r\n- sending messages with specified event\r\n- receiving messages with all types of events, as well as callbacks\r\n\r\nJava client doesn't support listening to all types of events, so I had to add like 2 lines of code in `.onevent()`. Unfortunately, due to client having nearly everything set to non-public I had to copy several of its files to make it work. I hope they add it someday, every other language has this functionality.\r\n\r\nAlso, there is one issue and I have no clue how to fix it. After making even a single connection to Socket.IO server and closing the program, one OpenJDK process remains for about 30 seconds, preventing the program from running and showing an error. {"id":1239098492,"created_at":"2022-05-17T20:01:03Z","updated_at":"2022-05-18T13:05:47Z","state":"closed","title":"How do you pull the co-ordinates of a Text from a StyleClassedTextArea when you right click?","html_url":"https://github.com/FXMisc/RichTextFX/issues/1111","body":"I'm trying to create a spell checker when you right click an incorrect word, you should be able to replace it with a suggestion.  \r\n\r\n![spell checker](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/41022205/168899490-ad281199-78eb-434a-98a8-b6adb02920f9.gif)\r\n\r\nI'm having trouble replacing the text because there is no way to get the co-ordinates of the Text.\r\n\r\nHere is the code:\r\n\r\n**pom.xml**\r\n\r\n        <dependency>\r\n            <groupId>org.fxmisc.richtext<\/groupId>\r\n            <artifactId>richtextfx<\/artifactId>\r\n            <version>0.10.6<\/version>\r\n        <\/dependency>\r\n        <dependency>\r\n            <groupId>org.apache.commons<\/groupId>\r\n            <artifactId>commons-text<\/artifactId>\r\n            <version>1.9<\/version>\r\n            <type>jar<\/type>\r\n        <\/dependency>\r\n\r\n**SpellCheckDemo.java**\r\n\r\n    import java.io.BufferedReader;\r\n    import java.io.IOException;\r\n    import java.io.InputStream;\r\n    import java.io.InputStreamReader;\r\n    import java.text.BreakIterator;\r\n    import java.time.Duration;\r\n    import java.util.Collection;\r\n    import java.util.Collections;\r\n    import java.util.HashSet;\r\n    import java.util.Set;\r\n    \r\n    import org.fxmisc.flowless.VirtualizedScrollPane;\r\n    import org.fxmisc.richtext.StyleClassedTextArea;\r\n    import org.fxmisc.richtext.model.StyleSpans;\r\n    import org.fxmisc.richtext.model.StyleSpansBuilder;\r\n    \r\n    import javafx.application.Application;\r\n    import javafx.scene.Scene;\r\n    import javafx.scene.control.ContextMenu;\r\n    import javafx.scene.control.MenuItem;\r\n    import javafx.scene.input.ContextMenuEvent;\r\n    import javafx.scene.layout.StackPane;\r\n    import javafx.scene.text.Text;\r\n    import javafx.stage.Stage;\r\n    import org.apache.commons.text.similarity.JaroWinklerDistance;\r\n    import org.reactfx.Subscription;\r\n    \r\n    public class SpellCheckingDemo extends Application\r\n    {\r\n    \r\n        private static final Set<String> dictionary = new HashSet<String>();\r\n        private final static double JAROWINKLERDISTANCE_THRESHOLD = .80;\r\n    \r\n        public static void main(String[] args)\r\n        {\r\n            launch(args);\r\n        }\r\n    \r\n        @Override\r\n        public void start(Stage primaryStage)\r\n        {\r\n            StyleClassedTextArea textArea = new StyleClassedTextArea();\r\n            textArea.setWrapText(true);\r\n    \r\n            Subscription cleanupWhenFinished = textArea.multiPlainChanges()\r\n                    .successionEnds(Duration.ofMillis(500))\r\n                    .subscribe(change ->\r\n                    {\r\n                        textArea.setStyleSpans(0, computeHighlighting(textArea.getText()));\r\n                    });\r\n            // call when no longer need it: `cleanupWhenFinished.unsubscribe();`\r\n    \r\n            textArea.setOnContextMenuRequested((ContextMenuEvent event) ->\r\n            {\r\n                if (event.getTarget() instanceof Text)\r\n                {\r\n                    Text text = (Text) event.getTarget();\r\n                    ContextMenu context = new ContextMenu();\r\n                    JaroWinklerDistance distance = new JaroWinklerDistance();\r\n                    for (String word : dictionary)\r\n                    {\r\n                        if (distance.apply(text.getText(), word) >= JAROWINKLERDISTANCE_THRESHOLD)\r\n                        {\r\n                            MenuItem item = new MenuItem(word);\r\n                            item.setOnAction(a ->\r\n                            {\r\n                                // how do I find the position of the Text object ?                    \r\n                                textArea.replaceText(25, 25 + text.getText().length(), word);\r\n                            });\r\n                            context.getItems().add(item);\r\n    \r\n                        }\r\n    \r\n                    }\r\n    \r\n                    context.show(primaryStage, event.getScreenX(), event.getScreenY());\r\n    \r\n                }\r\n            });\r\n    \r\n            // load the dictionary\r\n            try (InputStream input = SpellCheckingDemo.class.getResourceAsStream(\"/spellchecking.dict\");\r\n                    BufferedReader br = new BufferedReader(new InputStreamReader(input)))\r\n            {\r\n                String line;\r\n                while ((line = br.readLine()) != null)\r\n                {\r\n                    dictionary.add(line);\r\n                }\r\n            } catch (IOException e)\r\n            {\r\n                e.printStackTrace();\r\n            }\r\n    \r\n            // load the sample document\r\n            InputStream input2 = SpellCheckingDemo.class.getResourceAsStream(\"/spellchecking.txt\");\r\n            try (java.util.Scanner s = new java.util.Scanner(input2))\r\n            {\r\n                String document = s.useDelimiter(\"\\\\A\").hasNext() ? s.next() : \"\";\r\n                textArea.replaceText(0, 0, document);\r\n            }\r\n    \r\n            Scene scene = new Scene(new StackPane(new VirtualizedScrollPane<>(textArea)), 600, 400);\r\n            scene.getStylesheets().add(SpellCheckingDemo.class.getResource(\"/spellchecking.css\").toExternalForm());\r\n            primaryStage.setScene(scene);\r\n            primaryStage.setTitle(\"Spell Checking Demo\");\r\n            primaryStage.show();\r\n        }\r\n    \r\n        private static StyleSpans<Collection<String>> computeHighlighting(String text)\r\n        {\r\n    \r\n            StyleSpansBuilder<Collection<String>> spansBuilder = new StyleSpansBuilder<>();\r\n    \r\n            BreakIterator wb = BreakIterator.getWordInstance();\r\n            wb.setText(text);\r\n    \r\n            int lastIndex = wb.first();\r\n            int lastKwEnd = 0;\r\n            while (lastIndex != BreakIterator.DONE)\r\n            {\r\n                int firstIndex = lastIndex;\r\n                lastIndex = wb.next();\r\n    \r\n                if (lastIndex != BreakIterator.DONE\r\n                        && Character.isLetterOrDigit(text.charAt(firstIndex)))\r\n                {\r\n                    String word = text.substring(firstIndex, lastIndex).toLowerCase();\r\n                    if (!dictionary.contains(word))\r\n                    {\r\n                        spansBuilder.add(Collections.emptyList(), firstIndex - lastKwEnd);\r\n                        spansBuilder.add(Collections.singleton(\"underlined\"), lastIndex - firstIndex);\r\n                        lastKwEnd = lastIndex;\r\n                    }\r\n                    System.err.println();\r\n                }\r\n            }\r\n            spansBuilder.add(Collections.emptyList(), text.length() - lastKwEnd);\r\n    \r\n            return spansBuilder.create();\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n\r\nThe following files go into the resource folder: \r\n\r\n**spellchecking.css**\r\n\r\n    .underlined {\r\n        -rtfx-background-color: #f0f0f0;\r\n        -rtfx-underline-color: red;\r\n        -rtfx-underline-dash-array: 2 2;\r\n        -rtfx-underline-width: 1;\r\n        -rtfx-underline-cap: butt;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n**spellchecking.dict**\r\n\r\n    a\r\n    applied\r\n    basic\r\n    brown\r\n    but\r\n    could\r\n    document\r\n    dog\r\n    fox\r\n    here\r\n    if\r\n    is\r\n    its\r\n    jumps\r\n    lazy\r\n    no\r\n    over\r\n    quick\r\n    rendering\r\n    sample\r\n    see\r\n    styling\r\n    the\r\n    there\r\n    this\r\n    were\r\n    you\r\n\r\n**spellchecking.txt**\r\n\r\n    The quik brown fox jumps over the lazy dog.\r\n    Ths is a sample dokument.\r\n    There is no styling aplied, but if there were, you could see its basic rndering here.\r\n\r\n"}

{"id":1202314232,"created_at":"2022-04-12T19:47:10Z","updated_at":"2022-05-11T15:14:28Z","state":"closed","title":"Add inbound Tor connectivity test","html_url":"https://github.com/bisq-network/bisq/pull/6147","body":"A user set up Bisq on Whonix.  While Bisq appears to run correctly, their open offers were not able to be taken - rejected with the error message \"Maker is offline\".  After a while the user was contacted by the support team with a private notification suggesting they clear the Tor cache and restart (the normal suggested resolution for connectivity issues).\r\n\r\nThe user made a good suggestion that Bisq should do a test attempting to connect back to itself over Tor.  If that fails then show a message informing them to check their firewall configuration.  This PR implements that.  The test runs after Bisq has fully initialized.\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-04-12 13-24-34](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/47253594/163039123-c8b530c5-e71b-4fa7-8c5a-6153d3a1292a.png)\r\n\r\nFixes #6142\r\nFixes #6141\r\n\r\n### Testing\r\n\r\n- In a normal mainnet setup, ran Bisq and the connection to self was successful.\r\n- On Whonix, ran Bisq and the connection to self was unsuccessful resulting in the above popup.\r\n\r\n\r\n"}

{"id":1195244669,"created_at":"2022-04-06T22:24:15Z","updated_at":"2022-04-07T14:25:43Z","state":"closed","title":"JPMS related VM configurations cannot be set","html_url":"https://github.com/shannah/jdeploy/issues/56","body":"With the introduction of jpms, new java options are introduced:\r\n\r\n- With `--add-exports` the package is exported, meaning all public types and members therein are accessible at compile and run time.\r\n- With `--add-opens` the package is opened, meaning all types and members (not only public ones!) therein are accessible at run time.\r\n\r\nIn https://www.jdeploy.com/~osgifx application, I need the following java options to be set as well to make it work:\r\n\r\n```\r\n\"args\": [\r\n            \"--add-exports=javafx.base/com.sun.javafx.event=ALL-UNNAMED\",\r\n            \"--add-exports=javafx.base/com.sun.javafx.runtime=ALL-UNNAMED\",\r\n            \"--add-exports=javafx.graphics/com.sun.glass.ui=ALL-UNNAMED\",\r\n            \"--add-exports=javafx.graphics/com.sun.javafx.scene=ALL-UNNAMED\",\r\n            \"--add-exports=javafx.graphics/com.sun.javafx.application=ALL-UNNAMED\",\r\n            \"--add-exports=javafx.graphics/com.sun.glass.ui=ALL-UNNAMED\",\r\n            \"--add-exports=javafx.graphics/com.sun.javafx.css=ALL-UNNAMED\",\r\n            \"--add-opens=javafx.graphics/javafx.scene=ALL-UNNAMED\",\r\n            \"--add-opens=javafx.controls/javafx.scene.control.skin=ALL-UNNAMED\"\r\n        ],\r\n```\r\n\r\nThese options are still not set while running the application by either double clicking on it or by running the executable directly from the command line."}

{"id":1214397890,"created_at":"2022-04-25T11:56:32Z","updated_at":"2022-04-28T17:00:08Z","state":"closed","title":"lesson2","html_url":"https://github.com/kavaruDP/fm/pull/1","body":"-обновил sdk до ver11 и javafx до ver17.0.1\n-прикрутил к проекту javafx (из вебинара Александра Фисунова Разработка простого файлового менеджера)\n-создал две формы: для авторизации и для просмотра файлов с помощью локальной и \"серверной\" панелей\n-настроил навигацию по файлам в обеих панелях, серверная панель работает c ограничением каталога верхнего уровня.\nБлижние планы:\n-развернуть код из урока по netty\n-адаптировать серверную панель под работу с netty\n-закрыть в серверной панели возможность углубляться на уровень 4 и далее\nСредние планы:\n- настроить передачу файлов между панелями (с использованием netty)\nДальние планы:\n- подключить SqlLight, настроить в БД две таблицы (users и settings),\n- написать код для проверки логина/пароля через запрос к БД\n- написать код для регистрации новой учетной записи\n- написать код для хранения пароля в зашифрованном виде\n\nПроблемы:\nНе удалось пробросить в SecondaryController ссылки на контроллеры LocalPanelController и ServerPanelController\nВ ресурсном файле контролера SecondaryController эти контролеры вызваются следующим образом:\n        <fx:include fx:id=\"leftPanel\" source=\"localPanel.fxml\" HBox.hgrow=\"ALWAYS\"/>\n        <fx:include fx:id=\"rightPanel\" source=\"serverPanel.fxml\" HBox.hgrow=\"ALWAYS\"/>\n\nВариант\n    @FXML\n    LocalPanelController leftPC;\n    @FXML\n    ServerPanelController rightPC;\nоказался нерабочим (leftPC и rightPC не инициализируются).\n\nОбходное решение, которое сработало:\nИнициализация с помощью кода внутри SecondaryController:\n        leftPC = (LocalPanelController) leftPanel.getUserData();\n        rightPC = (ServerPanelController) rightPanel.getUserData();\n\nи вставка в ресурсные файлы localPanel.fxml и serverPanel.fxml кода\n    <userData>\n        <fx:reference source=\"controller\" />\n    <\/userData>\n"}

{"id":1204505857,"created_at":"2022-04-14T13:05:43Z","updated_at":"2022-05-01T04:21:28Z","state":"closed","title":"Updated library to handle passed image objects properly and entirely","html_url":"https://github.com/dustinkredmond/FXTrayIcon/pull/47","body":"The ```setGraphic(File)``` method when used with Java 18, throws an exception, because the method was first loading the file into a JavaFX Image object by passing the files ```.gatAbsolutePath``` property, and when passing a path String into JavaFX ```Image(path)```, if the path is not preceeded with ```file:```, it throws an Exception. I don't know if this is true with older versions of Java or not, but I assume not since no one mentioned the error previously.\r\n\r\nAs I thought about a solutionm to the problem, and studied the code, I realized something that I feel is rather important: FXTrayIcon initially required images to be passed in via a URL into the class constructors. But as the library has evolved, the needs of different developers necessitated some changes that added more options for the icon file itself and how it is passed into the library, and those additions were offred in the setGraphic methods.\r\n\r\nIt didn't make a lot of sense to me, to pass in a File object with the setGraphic method, then convert that File into a JavaFX Image, then use SwingFXUtilities to convert it into the required AWT Image object. So I wrote a ```loadImageFromFile``` method that simply takes the file and loads it directly into an AWT Image via FileStream. \r\n\r\nThis solved my problem.\r\n\r\nBut then, after looking things over, it also occured to me that it would be best to offer developers different options for passing in the image that becomes the icon for FXTI.\r\n\r\nSo, I created some overloaded ```loadImageFromFile``` private methods that handle different scenarios. But there is one more consideration required when rendering the final icon image in the tray and that is the size of the image needs to be different depending on which operating system is running the library.\r\n\r\nSince FXTrayIcon currently has TWO methods that allow a developer to pass in an icon image that can have any dimension at all without those dimensions being specified, I felt that it would be best to only allow TWO options for passing in an image object.\r\n\r\n1) Pass the object into FXTrayIcon without any dimensions, at which point, the library will set the dimensions of the image before using it.\r\n\r\n2) Pass the image object into FXTrayIcon with the specified dimensions along with it.\r\n\r\nSO, I CONSOLIDATED the various options for image objects that are currently accepted by the library, but in different scenarios, and I made all of those options available under all scenarios. Here are the scenarios:\r\n\r\nUnder the ```setGraphic``` method, these objects are accepted: \r\n\r\n- File Object - which gets its path extracted to a string, then a JavaFX object is created which is then converted into an AWT Image object.\r\n- AWT Image object - with no dimensions being required nor are any dimensions altered before the object is applied to the icon.\r\n- JavaFX Image object which is also never given dimensions and is merely converted to an AWT Image and assigned to the icon\r\n\r\nDuring FXTrayIcon class instantiation, these objects are accepted:\r\n\r\n- URL containing the path to the image file.\r\n  - Without dimensions specified - which are then assigned by the library\r\n  - WITH dimensions specified\r\n- No object at all in which case a default icon is used.\r\n\r\nThe Builder class follows the class constructors.\r\n\r\nWith these changes in this PR, I have consolidated all of the accepted objects so that they can all be used whether at instantiation or during runtime. I added the safety measure where when an object is passed into the library without any dimensions specified, the dimensions get assigned based on the OS. And if the object is passed into the library with dimensions, then the dimensions passed as argument get used.\r\n\r\n- Class constructors were created to handle all objects.\r\n- ```setGraphic``` methods have been added to handle all objects.\r\n- Builder class has been updated to mirror class constructors.\r\n- The private ```loadImageFrom``` methods have been renamed to reflect the object that they are loading (```loadImageFromURL``` etc.)\r\n\r\nSo with this PR, the following image objects can now be used by a developer both at instantiation as well as during runtime if desired:\r\n\r\n- java.io.File\r\n- javafx.scene.image.Image\r\n- java.net.URL\r\n- java.awt.Image\r\n\r\nThe use of SwingFXUtils is only employed when a JavaFX Image object is passed into the library. All other objects use the AWT method of creating an Image object which can accept URL or InputStream and in the case of a File object, the object is first assigned to an InputStream then the AWT Image is created from that.\r\n\r\nJavadoc comments have all been properly assigned to the relevant portions of the library.\r\n\r\nBackward compatibility has been completely maintained. An upgrade to this version of the libary will not affect any code that uses the current version of the library.\r\n\r\nAll changes have been tested - each and every one, and everything works flawlessly.\r\n"}

{"id":1127814622,"created_at":"2022-02-08T22:14:23Z","updated_at":"2022-04-28T20:34:20Z","state":"closed","title":"Module with javafx plugin is always considered out-of-date in a fresh gradle daemon","html_url":"https://github.com/openjfx/javafx-gradle-plugin/issues/123","body":"A Gradle module has the following configuration:\r\n```groovy\r\nplugins {\r\n\tid 'org.openjfx.javafxplugin' version '0.0.9'\r\n}\r\n\r\njavafx {\r\n\tconfiguration = 'api'\r\n\tversion = '17'\r\n\tmodules = ['javafx.base', 'javafx.controls', 'javafx.fxml', 'javafx.graphics', 'javafx.media', 'javafx.swing', 'javafx.web']\r\n}\r\n```\r\nThe module is reported as UP-TO-DATE when running assemble twice:\r\n```bash\r\ngradle assemble\r\ngradle assemble\r\n```\r\n\r\nI would now expect the module to be UP-TO-DATE when stopping the Gradle Daemon between the two assemble runs:\r\n```bash\r\ngradle assemble\r\ngradle --stopp\r\ngradle assemble\r\n```\r\n\r\nHowever this is not  the case. Strangely when ran with the `--info` switch, Gradle reports that the input property `Classpath` was changed and the module therefore needs to be rebuilt.\r\n```\r\nTask ':common-fx:compileJava' is not up-to-date because:\r\n  Input property 'classpath' file /home/ursl/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/org.openjfx/javafx-swing/17/8dee489b0faecf27568bfe64efdc7aa01410defa/javafx-swing-17-linux.jar has been removed.\r\n  Input property 'classpath' file /home/ursl/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/org.openjfx/javafx-web/17/bbd71beaf561b72f0d3eb6268d3114573b7799c3/javafx-web-17-linux.jar has been added.\r\n  Input property 'classpath' file /home/ursl/.gradle/caches/modules-2/files-2.1/org.openjfx/javafx-web/17/bbd71beaf561b72f0d3eb6268d3114573b7799c3/javafx-web-17-linux.jar has been removed.\r\n```\r\nEven more strangely, these reported changes are not consistent. The \"changed\" dependencies vary every time the above commands are repeated."}
{"id":1218700346,"created_at":"2022-04-28T13:03:33Z","updated_at":"2022-04-29T15:36:55Z","state":"closed","title":"FloatingText for DatePIcker","html_url":"https://github.com/palexdev/MaterialFX/issues/190","body":"MFXDatePicker is great, but, I would love for it to support floating text like almost all the rest of the fields.\r\n\r\nFor example, you can currently set prompt text to \"Birth Date\" and have a result as such:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/400362/165757446-e6460382-5cff-41ad-bd4e-0ab0e38fa51b.png)\r\n\r\nBut, the purpose of _prompt text_ is to provide the user with info on data format or idea, like so:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/400362/165757652-4a13048f-235c-48be-a6dd-a985eb7bc46f.png)\r\n\r\nOnce you select data, then you don't see the _prompt text_ any longer, since it isn't needed:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/400362/165757841-a306f37d-1a1c-48ef-a7ff-75d9f17cf91b.png)\r\n\r\nA floating text would solve that issue, for instance:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/400362/165757941-b74d4c2e-360e-47ef-95a3-ea6258ee6324.png)\r\n\r\nLastly, if you have multiple date fields, one for a birth date, another for x date and y date, when you edit the date, since the floating text isn't available, your three date fields won't have any indicator for what kind of info is the displayed data referred to, only if you manually add labels and most likely won't look as nice as the other fields.\r\n\r\n**UPDATE:**\r\nCurrent workaround:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/400362/165783049-79df2a03-d0bd-4724-a503-0b5f736d01ca.png)\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/400362/165783142-ba8b0de2-ac92-409e-909b-aa71ea3e321c.png)\r\n\r\n\r\nFXML:\r\n```xml\r\n<Pane layoutX=\"254.0\" layoutY=\"229.0\" prefHeight=\"51.0\" prefWidth=\"198.0\" styleClass=\"fieldset\">\r\n   <children>\r\n      <VBox alignment=\"CENTER\">\r\n         <HBox alignment=\"CENTER\">\r\n            <MFXDatePicker fx:id=\"birthDate\" prefHeight=\"51.0\" prefWidth=\"122.0\" promptText=\"DD/MM/YYYY\" />\r\n         <\/HBox>\r\n      <\/VBox>\r\n      <Label layoutX=\"8.0\" layoutY=\"-10.0\" styleClass=\"fieldset-title\" text=\"Birth Date\" />\r\n   <\/children>\r\n<\/Pane>\r\n```\r\n\r\n```css\r\n.fieldset {\r\n    -mfx-main: -mfx-purple;\r\n    -fx-background-color: white;\r\n    -fx-background-radius: 5;\r\n    -fx-border-color: lightgray;\r\n    -fx-border-radius: 5;\r\n    -fx-padding: 5;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.fieldset .fieldset-title {\r\n    -fx-padding: 0 3;\r\n    -fx-font-family: \"Open Sans Regular\";\r\n    -fx-text-fill: -mfx-text-he;\r\n    -fx-background-color: white;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.fieldset MFXDatePicker {\r\n    -fx-border-color: transparent;\r\n    -fx-background-color: transparent;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, the JavaFX CSS processor does not support `:has`, there fore something like the following isn't possible directly from CSS:\r\n\r\n```css\r\n.fieldset:has(.mfx-date-picker):has(:focus-within) {\r\n    -fx-border-color: -mfx-purple;\r\n}\r\n\r\n.fieldset:has(.mfx-date-picker):has(:focus-within) .fieldset-title {\r\n    -fx-text-fill: -mfx-purple;\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nThat way, when the enclosed `MFXDatePicker` filled had `focus-within`, it would set the fieldset border and label text colour to `-mfx-purple`"}

{"id":1197812132,"created_at":"2022-04-08T20:47:56Z","updated_at":"2022-05-28T14:57:21Z","state":"closed","title":"SvgImage.toImageScaled produces only uneven wide images (for uneven input)","html_url":"https://github.com/hervegirod/fxsvgimage/issues/13","body":"I'm trying to convert an SVG of a QR-Code to an Image. The QR-Code has a size of 25 (which is loaded correctly).\r\nUltimately there should be several sizes, all powers of 2, to be usable as icons, but the problem happens with any size.\r\n\r\nIf I enter a scale-factor that would produce the correct `width`, it instead returns an image with `width+1`.\r\nE.g. `qr.toImageScaled(64 / qr.getWidth)` will return an Image with `width` and `height` of `65` (instead of the desired `64`).\r\nFurthermore, outsmarting the algorithm doesn't work. `qr.toImageScaled(63 / 25)` produces an image of width `63`.\r\n\r\nPreliminary testing shows that it snaps to the next uneven number of pixels, rounded up.\r\n\r\nIs that a limitation of the rendering? I've seen you use a Scene to render a snapshot into an image, but am currently too tired to debug that far into it."}

{"id":1190254614,"created_at":"2022-04-01T20:45:11Z","updated_at":"2022-04-04T17:09:58Z","state":"closed","title":"\"Duplicate Image(s)\" attempts to parse regex expression in project entry name","html_url":"https://github.com/qupath/qupath/issues/942","body":"**Describe the bug**\r\nAttempting to duplicate a project entry containing an unclosed parenthesis (e.g. a left parenthesis `(` with no right parenthesis to follow) will throw an error, preventing the entry from being duplicated without renaming. Relatively minor issue, as a fix would be to simply rename the original entry before duplication.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce**\r\nSteps to reproduce the behavior:\r\n1. Create a project, loading an image named `OS-2.ndpi`\r\n2. Duplicate the project entry (via right click > Duplicate Image(s). No error will occur, duplicate image will be named `OS-2.ndpi (1)`\r\n3. Rename this duplicated image by removing the last parenthesis, to `OS-2.ndpi (1`\r\n4. Attempt to duplicate this image. Note the following error:\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/52012166/161337956-5eabd4e7-0b3e-4a29-8b1b-914e3484cda7.png)\r\nSee full log at the end.\r\n\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\nRegex patterns should not be evaluated for when duplicating image names. I'd imagine there are a lot of other character combinations that can trigger regex-related errors during duplication, or perhaps other operations too. I wonder if there's any cool things that can be done with this, such as programmatically creating image names during image duplication...\r\n\r\n**Desktop (please complete the following information):**\r\n - OS: Windows 10\r\n - QuPath Version: 0.4.0-SNAPSHOT\r\n\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\nFull error log:\r\n```\r\nERROR: QuPath exception: Unclosed group near index {"id":1218825443,"created_at":"2022-04-28T14:33:52Z","updated_at":"2022-05-03T16:51:03Z","state":"closed","title":"Multiple messages in the SnackBar","html_url":"https://github.com/JabRef/jabref/pull/8733","body":"<!-- \r\nDescribe the changes you have made here: what, why, ... \r\nLink issues that are fixed, e.g. \"Fixes #333\".\r\nIf you fixed a koppor issue, link it, e.g. \"Fixes https://github.com/koppor/jabref/issues/47\".\r\nThe title of the PR must not reference an issue, because GitHub does not support autolinking there.\r\n-->\r\nThanks to @EduRibeiro00 & @X1nbb for documenting the findings and working on this issue. ❤️ \r\n\r\n## **Previous Discussion for Handling Multiple Messages**: #7577 #7968 \r\nFrom the [Snackbars Design Guidelines](https://material.io/components/snackbars#usage) the frequency of the Snackbar should be only once at a time is recommended. I believe the implementation of https://github.com/sshahine/JFoenix/blob/2dbb8515da236140c41eabe22eb549b458f1e867/jfoenix/src/main/java/com/jfoenix/controls/JFXSnackbar.java#L321 is also based on that. The ideal choice to show Multiple Messages would be moving from Snackbar to Notifications (with custom CSS changes to replicate snack bar design) \r\n\r\n## **Proposed Solution**: _Moving from Snackbar to Notifcations_ \r\nFixes #7340 \r\n```\r\nNotifications notificationBuilder = Notifications.create()\r\n        .text(message)\r\n        .position(Pos.BOTTOM_CENTER)\r\n        .threshold(5, thresholdNotification)\r\n        .hideAfter(TOAST_MESSAGE_DISPLAY_TIME)\r\n        .hideCloseButton();\r\nnotificationBuilder.show();\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17572818/164216381-f49be03d-421b-44a4-ab50-c7cc9e3a9a9a.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n## **Few Open Questions while Implementation**:\r\n- The Maximum Notification is set as `5`, as per the current draft PR. I have displayed a threshold notification that says `\"Too much happening... Hang on..\"` **_Can someone suggest a better UX/message/way handle this, let's discuss._** \r\n- For a different workflow, I tried accessing the inner class of Notification. And ended up with this error `“Unable to make private void org.controlsfx.control.Notifications$NotificationPopupHandler.hide(javafx.stage.Popup,javafx.geometry.Pos) accessible: module org.controlsfx.controls does not \"opens org.controlsfx.control\" to module org.jabref”.` If someone suggests **_how to resolve this?_** I thought of removing the threshold notification and hiding the top of the stack with the help of this while inserting the next incoming notification.\r\n\r\n\r\n## PR Checklist:\r\n\r\n- [ ] Change in `CHANGELOG.md` described in a way that is understandable for the average user (if applicable)\r\n- [ ] Tests created for changes (if applicable)\r\n- [x] Manually tested changed features in running JabRef (always required)\r\n- [x] Screenshots added in PR description (for UI changes)\r\n- [ ] [Checked developer's documentation](https://devdocs.jabref.org/): Is the information available and up to date? If not, I outlined it in this pull request.\r\n- [ ] [Checked documentation](https://docs.jabref.org/): Is the information available and up to date? If not, I created an issue at <https://github.com/JabRef/user-documentation/issues> or, even better, I submitted a pull request to the documentation repository.\r\n\r\n"}
{"id":1124980611,"created_at":"2022-02-05T17:02:38Z","updated_at":"2022-05-19T17:54:35Z","state":"closed","title":"thoughts on Swing for version 2.8.2","html_url":"https://github.com/kunstmusik/blue/issues/645","body":"i will give show some differences on the Roboto version of Blue. Because, as i understand it, reliable working with JavaFX in Blue cannot be trusted upon in the future, JavaFX will make room for Swing.\r\n\r\n1. much faster, feel lighter in use, responds quicker\r\n2. reliable for years to come\r\n\r\nConverting existing instruments to Swing and Roboto:\r\n1. here a comparison of the same instrument, designed with JavaFX\r\n![JavaFX](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6670911/152650185-8d6d9cb3-4eeb-43a7-b02e-c251607690d5.png)\r\nthis is the Swing version:\r\n![Swing](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6670911/152650200-a10da2a6-2240-4482-92e2-a9ba302de8c9.png)\r\n\r\nFont and knobs are smaller.\r\nAdvantage IMO is that now there is more room for displaying more value numbers. That is useful\r\nJavaFX: \r\n![JavaFXknobs](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6670911/152650351-5fb82a8c-5496-4bcb-8f1a-432bc7bb635e.png)\r\nSwing:\r\n![Swingknobs](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6670911/152650361-9d4a4736-67be-435a-9f54-4708d950bed4.png)\r\n\r\nAdvantage IMO of Roboto is the smaller and less bold type of font. This allows instruments and effects to become smaller.\r\nAnd personally i don't mind redoing all my instrument and effects, now that i know that they will like that in 10 years from now...\r\n\r\nA problem is that all sliders do not get the values like they were saved. I loose all presets and saved values in the blue files. \r\nAnother thing is that the sliders are aesthetically not pleasing. Of course, IMO.\r\n\r\n\r\nThen about the Editing response: it feels sluggish\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/6670911/152651095-ef32d998-1104-4aaa-90cd-2d0189bd93e6.mp4\r\n\r\nthe sliders respond VERY fast, the knobs also. Nice also, that it is possible to be able to make fine adjustments with the knobs.\r\n"}

{"id":1211037783,"created_at":"2022-04-21T13:20:58Z","updated_at":"2022-05-25T10:21:36Z","state":"closed","title":"Windows Native EXE with externall DLL - JavaCPP loader crashes","html_url":"https://github.com/gluonhq/substrate/issues/1144","body":"### MY PROJECT :\r\n**Uses 2 parts :**\r\n- 1x 100% Java\r\n- 1x External DLL coming from C++, which I built with JavaCPP\r\n\r\n**I use Eclipse IDE** and the latest plugins / GraalVM as you will see in my POM and logs.\r\n\r\n**All works fine with JavaFx goal : javafx:run**\r\n\r\n**All works fine with Gluon goal : gluonfx:build** ([GluonBuild.log](https://github.com/gluonhq/substrate/files/8530981/GluonBuild.log))\r\n\r\n### PROBLEM :\r\n**If I make it on purpose to 'hide' the external DLL.**\r\nAll works fine with Gluon goal : gluonfx:nativerun ([GluonNativeRun_NoDLL.log](https://github.com/gluonhq/substrate/files/8531010/GluonNativeRun_NoDLL.log))\r\n\r\n**With external DLL found, app crashes with a 'Error loading class org/bytedeco/javacpp/Loader'** ([GluonNativeRun_WithDLL.log](https://github.com/gluonhq/substrate/files/8531034/GluonNativeRun_WithDLL.log)\r\n- Line 55 of log says `com.company.Loader.loadLibFromPath(Loader.java:74)` which is this part of code :\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/32061339/164460263-0ad29f68-6cae-4c78-8dfe-61d433ad36fb.png)\r\n- Line 44 of log says `Caused by: java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: Lorg/bytedeco/javacpp/Loader;` Which is the result of the problem on line 36 : `Error loading class org/bytedeco/javacpp/Loader`... But... my investigations show that the JAR and method path are there...\r\n\r\nI want to switch from Launch4J to Gluon in order to be able to port my app to different OS. But to test the architecture of my app, I have built, from exact same source code, an executable JAR to see if Launch4J would also give any error... Which is NOT the case. My app runs smoothly.\r\n\r\nTHREE differences though between both EXE build origins, mainly coming from the Maven building, needed for Gluon :\r\n1. I build separate JARs for Gluon (and reference them in my POM, attached [here](https://github.com/gluonhq/substrate/files/8531110/pom.txt))\r\n2. These are NOT executable JARs (as it is in Launch4J, which has just that one)\r\n3. The 'loading' part is done with a similar way, except that for Gluon EXE : the DLL is first 'extracted' from the resources inside the built JAR. Ending with the same instruction : `'System.load(temp.getAbsolutePath());'`.\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/32061339/164463217-a51e9ce5-f92d-4f80-86a6-c5637d241521.png)\r\n\r\n### CONCLUSION :\r\nI have tried really hard to understand why it would not work in Gluon.\r\n- The POM does reference de JavaCPP.\r\n- The path to the method inside the JavaCPP JAR does exists at the correct location.\r\n- I'm irritated from the line 31 which says :`WARNING: Unsupported JavaFX configuration: classes were loaded from 'unnamed module @531e85'` but I don't think this might be the issue.\r\n- In the building part, all Classes / Fields / Methods are not what Gluon says 'reachable' (lines 51 - 55 of GluonBuild.log). Does this matter ?\r\n \r\nOr... Is it that this is too complex for Gluon Substrate ?\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThank you for any help or clues... I'll investigate them !"}

{"id":1201354191,"created_at":"2022-04-12T08:00:30Z","updated_at":"2022-04-14T11:31:14Z","state":"closed","title":"Updated setGraphic(File) method","html_url":"https://github.com/dustinkredmond/FXTrayIcon/pull/46","body":"The updateGraphic(File file) method when used with Java 18, throws an exception, because when loading a JavaFX Image from a file path, it has to be preceded with the word \"file:\" - and I can't remember if that is also true of Java 1.8, but I tend to think it's not.\r\n\r\nSo I updated the method to catch the error if it's thrown, then it will prepend the path to the file with \"file:\" and then it loads the image and keeps moving along... \r\n\r\nTested it in GistFX and it works properly."}

Not just the one that was selected. In the picture attached, i selected the second entry from top to delete, which it did, but the first entry from top also vanished.\r\n- Groups become unresponsive#\r\n- When clicking on another group, there will be another error.\r\n- Entry editor sometimes needs more clicks to open.\r\n\r\n### Additional notes\r\n\r\n- Deleting the entries via the *DEL* key on my keyboard did not trigger any errors! Haven't tested that one too much yet, though.\r\n- Selecting the first entry on top of the list does not trigger any errors\r\n- The errors only happen when {}bibtex source is selected. {"id":1202254278,"created_at":"2022-04-12T18:44:24Z","updated_at":"2022-04-16T10:20:17Z","state":"closed","title":"BREAKING: Arch proposal","html_url":"https://github.com/RPG-IO/rpg-io/pull/13","body":"# Description\r\n\r\nProposal of the new architecture\r\n\r\n## How it works\r\n\r\n* Whole world is loaded from configuration files via `Initializer` class into `Game` class\r\n* `Game` class holds reference to `Controller` and is main class of our application. It was separated from the controller to make menu addition possible (it should be happening there)\r\n* `Controller` holds references to current `LocationModel` (which holds all the logical state concerning location being currently displayed) & current `LocationView` (which holds all the data needed for representation of model).\r\n* `LocationView` additionaly (as a `Scene` subclass) is responsible for collecting user **keyboard** input. When it receives one, it passes it to the controller via [`observer pattern`](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Observer_pattern). Controller then decides what to do (updates model -> model notifies view).\r\n* Each model class (GameObject, etc.) has its own counterpart - <className>View (e.g. GameObjectView). This serves main purpouse of separating representation from the data. \r\n* Classes such as `GameObjectView` are responsible for collecting user **mouse input**. If one is collected it is passed to controller via `observer pattern`.\r\n* `Controller` is responsible for updating **the model** basing on input it receives.\r\n* `Model` after update notifies `View` so the latter can update itself. \r\n\r\nThis way we achieve **almost** Model-View-Controller pattern!"}

Azután ugyan ilyen pull request-et csinálunk mint amit itt csinálok.\r\n<br>**Ahogy látom a github nem tudja autómatikusan merge-elni a két branch-et. {"id":973542184,"created_at":"2021-08-18T11:01:16Z","updated_at":"2022-05-16T19:04:13Z","state":"closed","title":"Find and replace an existing group while selecting {}bibtex source leads to error","html_url":"https://github.com/JabRef/jabref/issues/7999","body":"### JabRef version\r\n\r\nLatest development branch build\r\n\r\nJabRef 5.4--2021-08-15--96061b7\r\nJava 16.0.2 \r\nJavaFX 16+8\r\n\r\n### Operating system\r\n\r\nWindows 10\r\n\r\n### Details on version and operating system\r\n\r\nWindows 10, 10.0 amd64, 21H1\r\n\r\n### Checked with the latest development build\r\n\r\n- [X] I made a backup of my libraries before testing the latest development version.\r\n- [X] I have tested the latest development version and the problem persists\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n\r\n1. create a group called **test 1**\r\n2. add at least two entries to the group **test 1**\r\n3. click on group **test 1** (when in another group, the error will not show up!)\r\n4. click on one of the entries (i think it has to be an entry that is not the first in the list of entries? not sure about this condition!) within **test 1**, open the entry editor and go to the tab **{}bibtex source**\r\n5. use the find and replace function to replace **test 1** with another group (it does not matter if that new group is already in the library or not). Let's call the other group **test 4**.\r\n\r\n### What happens:\r\n\r\n- Error messages\r\n- Some entries become unresponsive. The entry editor doesn't open for them with a single click, but needs multiple clicks.\r\n- Groups become unresponsive.\r\n- A single file remains in group **test 1**, even though (for that file) the the {}bibtex source frame showed test 4! All other entries were moved to test 4. Manually editing that entry does not resolve the issue. If manually changing that entries group back from **test 4** to **test 1**, a DUPLICATE will show up in group 1, but the dublicate is unresponsive and can't be opened with the entry editor.\r\n\r\n### Why?\r\n\r\nEdit: I don't know\r\n\r\n### Things that seem to help:**\r\n- Selecting the first entry in the group does not lead to an error and abnormal behaviours.\r\n\r\n### Additional notes\r\nFind {"id":1213219996,"created_at":"2022-04-23T06:28:11Z","updated_at":"2022-05-07T21:07:18Z","state":"closed","title":"Update Java to version 17 LTS.","html_url":"https://github.com/WPISoftEng/CS3733-Starter-Code/pull/19","body":"This version includes the following changes:\r\n- Updates Java from version 11 to 17\r\n- Updates Gradle from 6.2 to 7.4.2\r\n- Switches from JFoenix to MaterialFX\r\n  - This is for a few reasons\r\n    **1.** JFoenix is mostly abandoned by its maintainer. MaterialFX was get's frequent updates and PRs\r\n    **2.** Certain JFoenix elements simply do not work on any Java version over 16\r\n    **3.** MaterialFX was made as a direct response to JFoenix no longer being updated and is generally more supported by the community, including OpenJFX.\r\n- Updated all plugins and implementations to the newest versions\r\n  - This includes updating JavaFX to support M1 Macs out of the box.\r\n- Optimized Gradle configs to decrease build time\r\n  - Enabled parallelization during build & tests\r\n  - Changed Gradle daemon JVM args to allow for more memory and use G1 garbage collection\r\n- Adds ShadowJar as a plugin in order to simplify the jar building process.\r\n- Removed references to Travis-CI due to it now being paid.\r\n- Removed no-longer supported/dead maven repositories"}

{"id":1193124379,"created_at":"2022-04-05T13:05:21Z","updated_at":"2022-04-19T20:02:00Z","state":"closed","title":"Add API for building JavaFX scene graph for transient diagram views","html_url":"https://github.com/osate/osate2/issues/2778","body":"It would be helpful to have an API that produces a JavaFX scene graph of a transient diagram-like view.  This API would allow plugins to make use of the rendering and layout capabilities of the OSATE graphical editor.\r\n\r\nThe JavaFX nodes for the individual graphics are exposed but using those nodes requires the plugin developer to build the scene graph with those nodes. Visualizing an AADL model using those nodes would require significant effort and duplication of the capabilities of the graphical editor.\r\n\r\nThe components for building a scene graph and using ELK to layout that scene graph is internal. Add an API that will wrap those internal components into a basic API that can remain stable as changes are made to the API.  Needed capabilities:\r\n\r\n- Create a scene graph for a diagram-like visualization of model elements. API should allow specifying which elements are to be visualized.\r\n- Allow applying styles to nodes\r\n- Provide bi-directional mapping between the requested model elements and the scene graph nodes.\r\n- Enable visualizing business objects which are not supported by the graphical editor by allowing specifying additional business object handlers."}

{"id":1209529007,"created_at":"2022-04-20T11:05:04Z","updated_at":"2022-04-28T14:43:36Z","state":"closed","title":"Internal PR for Team 22-7 #7340","html_url":"https://github.com/yogeshvar/jabref/pull/1","body":"Thanks to @EduRibeiro00 & @X1nbb for documenting the findings and working on this issue. ❤️ \r\n\r\n**Issue:** \r\n>  If JabRef has to display several messages very shortly after each other, the messages are stacked and played one after each other. This is confusing since the snack bar is still displaying a message, which is already obsolete. E.g. if you cycle quickly through the preview styles. \r\n\r\n## **Proposal for Handling Multiple Messages**:\r\n\r\nFrom the [Snackbars Design Guidelines](https://material.io/components/snackbars#usage) the frequency of the Snackbar should be only once at a time is recommended. I believe the implementation of https://github.com/sshahine/JFoenix/blob/2dbb8515da236140c41eabe22eb549b458f1e867/jfoenix/src/main/java/com/jfoenix/controls/JFXSnackbar.java#L321 is also based on that. The ideal choice to show Multiple Messages would be moving from Snackbar to Notifications (with custom CSS changes to replicate snack bar design)\r\n\r\n## **Proposed Solution**: _Moving from Snackbar to Notifcations_\r\n```\r\nNotifications notificationBuilder = Notifications.create()\r\n        .text(message)\r\n        .position(Pos.BOTTOM_CENTER)\r\n        .threshold(5, thresholdNotification)\r\n        .hideAfter(TOAST_MESSAGE_DISPLAY_TIME)\r\n        .hideCloseButton();\r\nnotificationBuilder.show();\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/17572818/164216381-f49be03d-421b-44a4-ab50-c7cc9e3a9a9a.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n## **Few Open Questions while Implementation**:\r\n\r\n- The Maximum Notification is set as `5`, as per the current draft PR. I have displayed a threshold notification that says `\"Too much happening.. Hang on..\"` Can someone suggest a better UX/message/way to handle this? \r\n\r\n- For a different workflow, I tried accessing the inner class of Notification. And ended up with this error “Unable to make private void org.controlsfx.control.Notifications$NotificationPopupHandler.hide(javafx.stage.Popup,javafx.geometry.Pos) accessible: module org.controlsfx.controls does not \"opens org.controlsfx.control\" to module org.jabref”. If someone suggest how to resolve this? I thought of removing the threshold notification and hide the top of the stack with the help of this while inserting the next incoming notification.\r\n\r\n\r\n## **Futuristic Scope/Idea**:\r\n\r\nHaving an activity log in JabRef would be great for the users to know what happens inside the application. If we have a story/issue for it. I have made an alternative implementation of Queue based Notifications that can be used to display in the Activity Log. \r\n\r\n\r\n``` private final Runnable updater = () -> {\r\n    Notifications thresholdNotification = Notifications.create().text(\"Too much happening.. Hang on..\").hideAfter(Duration.seconds(3));\r\n    synchronized (messageQueue) {\r\n        for (String message : messageQueue) {\r\n            Notifications.create().text(message).position(Pos.BOTTOM_CENTER)\r\n                    .threshold(5, thresholdNotification)\r\n                    .hideAfter(TOAST_MESSAGE_DISPLAY_TIME)\r\n                    .hideCloseButton().show();\r\n        }\r\n        // use message queue to show it activity log.\r\n        messageQueue.clear();\r\n        updating = false;\r\n    }\r\n};\r\n\r\n\r\n@Override\r\npublic void notify(String message) {\r\n    LOGGER.info(message);\r\n    synchronized (messageQueue) {\r\n        messageQueue.add(message);\r\n        if (!updating) {\r\n            updating = true;\r\n            Platform.runLater(updater);\r\n        }\r\n    }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n## PR Checklist:\r\n\r\n- [ ] Change in `CHANGELOG.md` described in a way that is understandable for the average user (if applicable)\r\n- [ ] Tests created for changes (if applicable)\r\n- [x] Manually tested changed features in running JabRef (always required)\r\n- [x] Screenshots added in PR description (for UI changes)\r\n- [ ] [Checked developer's documentation](https://devdocs.jabref.org/): Is the information available and up to date? If not, I outlined it in this pull request.\r\n- [ ] [Checked documentation](https://docs.jabref.org/): Is the information available and up to date? If not, I created an issue at <https://github.com/JabRef/user-documentation/issues> or, even better, I submitted a pull request to the documentation repository.\r\n"}

{"id":1042004718,"created_at":"2021-11-02T08:17:23Z","updated_at":"2022-03-29T09:42:04Z","state":"closed","title":"Remove OpenJFX dependencies while publishing to mvncentral","html_url":"https://github.com/palexdev/MaterialFX/pull/116","body":"Currently when you add the project as a dependency to any maven project, you get the following IDE error:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/25760501/139809363-d8a3e29d-00a3-4533-8b13-973cf0d3df19.png)\r\n\r\nThis is happening because the dependency MaterialFX is providing javafx dependencies, that should not be happening. Hence a workaround I am using is to add the following exclusions in my `pom.xml`:\r\n\r\n```XML\r\n<dependency>\r\n  <groupId>io.github.palexdev<\/groupId>\r\n  <artifactId>materialfx<\/artifactId>\r\n  <version>${materialfx.version}<\/version>\r\n  <exclusions>\r\n    <exclusion>\r\n       <groupId>org.openjfx<\/groupId>\r\n       <artifactId>javafx-graphics<\/artifactId>\r\n    <\/exclusion>\r\n    <exclusion>\r\n      <groupId>org.openjfx<\/groupId>\r\n      <artifactId>javafx-controls<\/artifactId>\r\n    <\/exclusion>\r\n    <exclusion>\r\n       <groupId>org.openjfx<\/groupId>\r\n       <artifactId>javafx-base<\/artifactId>\r\n    <\/exclusion>\r\n    <exclusion>\r\n      <groupId>org.openjfx<\/groupId>\r\n      <artifactId>javafx-swing<\/artifactId>\r\n    <\/exclusion>\r\n  <\/exclusions>\r\n<\/dependency>\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis PR removes the OpenJFX dependencies before publishing, hence solving the issue.\r\n"}

{"id":1124768166,"created_at":"2022-02-05T01:39:06Z","updated_at":"2022-05-12T13:06:36Z","state":"closed","title":"Builder API inconsistent","html_url":"https://github.com/dustinkredmond/FXTrayIcon/issues/42","body":"Why is ` URL iconImagePath` required to be passed into the builder constructor and not via a method? If the idea is to put required arguments in the constructor, then this doesn't make sense because there's a `setGraphic()` method, but no corresponding `graphic()` method for the builder. I see that it is probably to match the existing non-builder constructors, but I still think there should be a `graphic()`  method and possibly others for the size. In any case, it seems a good idea to have the builders constructors and methods match the original, if possible.\r\n\r\nThe API is `setTooltip()`, but `toolTip()` in the builder, whereas I think it should be `tooltip()`.  It seems to be an inconsistency in AWT vs. JavaFX naming. I believe the AWT method uses a capital 'T', but JavaFX uses a lowercase 't' by convention.\r\n\r\nThere's a `setTrayIconTooltip()` API which does the same thing, but the builder doesn't have such a method."}

When a command is executed, provided the command is a valid command, `SummaryList` will be updated by passing in the new list of applications for it to get the relevant statistics and update with a new list of `SummaryBox`.\r\n\r\n## Preview\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/24515765/160668046-cd1a8c4e-40e3-450a-a787-890e1c81fc54.png)\r\n\r\n## Other Updates\r\n- Fix README.md and index.md UI image link to the updated MainWindowUI.png\r\n- Manually tested each command with respect to the summary bar\r\n- Automated tests passed 267/267\r\n\r\n## Further improvements\r\n1. Any clue what I am doing wrong here?\r\nHere the code for my `UpdateHandler` implementation:\r\n```\r\npackage fr.antoninruan.maobootstrap;\r\n\r\nimport javafx.application.Platform;\r\nimport DialogUtils.loadingInfo(primaryStage);\r\n        downloadInfo.getValue().setText(\"Recherche de mise à jour\");\r\n\r\n        checkUpdates.setOnSucceeded(event -> {\r\n            Thread run = new Thread(() -> {\r\n               config.launch(this);\r\n            });\r\n\r\n            if (checkUpdates.getValue()) {\r\n                Task<Void> doUpdates = new Task<>() {\r\n                    @Override\r\n                    protected Void call() throws Exception {\r\n                        Path zip = Paths.get(\"temp.zip\");\r\n                        if (config.update(UpdateOptions.archive(zip).updateHandler(Updater.this)).getException() == null) {\r\n                            System.out.println(\"installé\");\r\n                            Archive.read(zip).install();\r\n                        }\r\n                        return null;\r\n                    }\r\n                };\r\n\r\n                run(doUpdates);\r\n            }\r\n\r\n//            run.start();\r\n\r\n        });\r\n\r\n        run(checkUpdates);\r\n\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    private Task<Boolean> checkUpdates() {\r\n        return new Task<>() {\r\n updateDownloadFileProgress(FileMetadata file, float frac) throws Throwable {\r\n        Platform.runLater(() -> {\r\n            downloadInfo.getValue().setText(\"Downloading \" + file.getPath().getFileName());\r\n        });\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    @Override\r\n    public void updateDownloadProgress(float frac) throws Throwable {\r\n        Platform.runLater(() -> {\r\n            downloadInfo.getKey().setProgress(frac);\r\n        });\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    @Override\r\n    public void failed(Throwable t) {\r\n        System.out.println(t.getMessage());\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    @Override\r\n    public void succeeded() {\r\n        System.out.println(\"Succès\");\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    @Override\r\n    public void stop() {\r\n        System.out.println(\"Arrêt\");\r\n {"id":1174297766,"created_at":"2022-03-19T16:07:10Z","updated_at":"2022-03-20T15:27:58Z","state":"closed","title":"Copy command branch","html_url":"https://github.com/AY2122S2-CS2103T-T13-4/tp/pull/78","body":"### Copy contacts in list: `copy`\r\n\r\nCopy the people within address book. Attach a clipboard to the side of CLI to copy data.\r\n\r\nFormat: `copy [INDEX] [n/NAME] [p/PHONE] [e/EMAIL] [a/ADDRESS] [s/STATUS] [m/MODULE] [f/FORMAT]​`\r\n\r\n* Copy persons using specified field names.​\r\n* If no fields are specified, all fields will be copied.\r\n* Choose INDEX to copy a specific person.\r\n* If no INDEX is specified, all persons will be copied.\r\n* Choice of format is default, csv and json. (\"default\", \"csv\", \"json\")\r\n* Default simply displays attribute, while csv format separates attributes via a \"|\" delimiter.\r\n* JSON format is a JSON object with attribute names as keys and attribute values as values, similar to application's save file.\r\n* Order of field names determines the order of attributes in the output.\r\n\r\nExamples:\r\n* `copy 1 n/ p/ e/ f/json`  will copy name, phone and email of first person in JSON format.\r\n* `copy f/csv` will copy the entire list in csv format.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/41231584/159128711-daeffb20-1cdd-4364-86fe-6d35e6239de2.png)\r\n\r\n"}

{"id":1153754152,"created_at":"2022-02-28T07:36:28Z","updated_at":"2022-03-03T03:44:48Z","state":"closed","title":"Attempting to run in archlinux results in the software crashing","html_url":"https://github.com/Querz/mcaselector/issues/339","body":"Java Version: `jre-openjdk 17.0.3.u3-1`\r\nJavaFX Version: `java-openjfx 17.0.3.u0-1`\r\n\r\n- as you can see, near enough the same version that it should work fine\r\n  \r\nMcaSelector Version - mcaselector-1.17.2.jar\r\n\r\nCommandline to launch \r\n`java -jar mcaselector-1.17.2.jar --module-path \"/usr/lib/jvm/java-17-openjdk/lib/\" --add-modules ALL-MODULE-PATH`\r\n\r\n\r\nThe Software crashes with this response:\r\n\r\n`failed to create directory /etc/xdg/mcaselector: /etc/xdg/mcaselector(AccessDeniedException)`\r\n`failed to create directory /etc/xdg/mcaselector: /etc/xdg/mcaselector(AccessDeniedException)`\r\n`[17:26:05.973] error: missing mode`\r\n\r\nFrom these lines alone, This appears to be trying to use the system default xdg location for xdg configurations as specified in `$XDG_CONFIG_DIRS`  (which if unspecified in the environment variables, should default to `/etc/xdg/`) instead it should default to the user configuration directory as specified in `$XDG_CONFIG_HOME`  which if unspecified should default to `$HOME/.config/` - with `$HOME` being an environment variable defined upon user login to identify what and where the user's home directory is.\r\n\r\n`$HOME/.config` is pretty much the linux version of `%appdata%` with the alternative directory being `$HOME/.local/share/`\r\n\r\nAs you can see, this is resulting in a permissions error - the permissions of `/etc/xdg/` make it so that that directory can only be written by its owner, which is the root user, or the system administrator account, and it makes no sense to write files that have to do with a piece of user software in a system configuration directory\r\n\r\nI have seen this issue pop up in closed bug reports like report #285 - but this is unique as i am not using an incorrect or incompatible version of java or javafx - both of these are the latest from the official archlinux repository and should work fine together. It might have something to do with my XDG desktop configuration (running XFCE4) but all my XDG configs are the default for this window manager anyway."}

{"id":1170346245,"created_at":"2022-03-15T22:58:01Z","updated_at":"2022-03-24T09:41:35Z","state":"closed","title":"Improve JPMS support: linking native jars into the jlink image","html_url":"https://github.com/bytedeco/gradle-javacpp/pull/20","body":"When running JPMS applications, JavaCPP users should only declare, in their module descriptor, the platform-independent module they need. For instance:\r\n```\r\nrequires org.bytedeco.opencv\r\n```\r\nThe platform-dependent native modules need to be added to the module graph with `--add-modules` command line argument when running the application, and when building an image with jlink.\r\n\r\nSince the module path is automatically populated with the needed native jars by Maven (using the `javacpp.platform` property)\r\nor by the Gradle plugin (using the `javacppPlatform` extra property), `--add-modules ALL-MODULE-PATH` is enough for running the application.\r\n\r\nFor building a JLink image with Maven, we can use the Apache Maven JLink plugin that automatically generates a `--add-modules` from the modules found in the module path.\r\nBut with Gradle, we have nothing similar. If we use the JavaFX Gradle plugin or the Badass jlink plugin, there is no such auto-generated `--add-modules` and thus the native modules are not added to the image.\r\nIf we configure Badass jlink plugin with `--add-module ALL-MODULE-PATH`, the image will contain all JavaCPP native modules\r\nbut also all the standard modules from the JDK, ruining most of the interest of building a custom runtime with jlink.\r\n\r\nThis PR adds the computation of a native module list that can be used in the Badass JLink plugin configuration to generate a proper `--add-module` argument.\r\nIt defines a javacpp extension to the platform plugin that contains the `plaforms` property and the `nativeModules` property.\r\nThe `nativeModules` property is computed during execution after the `classes` task (since it uses the runtime classpath, which can be modified during task execution), so must be added to the jlink task configuration in a `doFirst` block.\r\nThe `platforms` property replaces the `javacppPlatforms` extension property, but configuring the extra property is still supported for backward compatibility. Directly using the `platforms` property in a `javacpp` DSL block looks just a bit better.\r\nMore configurations for the JavaCPP plugin could be added later in this extension.\r\nHere is an example of build script with kotlin syntax:\r\n\r\n```Kotlin\r\nplugins {\r\n    application\r\n    id(\"org.bytedeco.gradle-javacpp-platform\") version \"1.5.8-SNAPSHOT\"\r\n    id(\"org.beryx.jlink\") version \"2.25.0\"\r\n}\r\n\r\njavacpp {\r\n  platforms = listOf(\"linux-x86_64\")\r\n}\r\n\r\ndependencies {\r\n    implementation(\"org.bytedeco:opencv-platform:4.5.5-1.5.7\")\r\n}\r\n\r\ngroup = \"org.bytedeco\"\r\nversion = \"1.0-SNAPSHOT\"\r\ndescription = \"gradle-jlink-sample\"\r\n\r\napplication {\r\n    mainModule.set(\"org.bytedeco.sample\")\r\n    mainClass.set(\"org.bytedeco.sample.Application\")\r\n    applicationDefaultJvmArgs = listOf(\"--add-modules\", \"ALL-MODULE-PATH\")\r\n}\r\n\r\ntasks.jlink {\r\n  doFirst {\r\n    jlink {\r\n      options.set(listOf(\"--add-modules\", javacpp.nativeModules))\r\n      launcher {\r\n        jvmArgs = listOf(\"--add-modules\", javacpp.nativeModules)\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nNote that the JavaFX gradle plugin doesn't allow to configure `--add-modules` for jlink, and is not needed anyway to run or link applications using JavaFX."}

{"id":1113238802,"created_at":"2022-01-24T23:08:48Z","updated_at":"2022-02-21T03:35:41Z","state":"closed","title":"Warn user when comparing graphs of the same name","html_url":"https://github.com/constellation-app/constellation/pull/1618","body":"<!--\r\n\r\n### Requirements\r\n\r\n* Filling out the template is required. Any pull request that does not include\r\nenough information to be reviewed in a timely manner may be closed at the\r\nmaintainers' discretion.\r\n* All new code requires unit tests to ensure they work as expected and will\r\ncontinue to work as new code is added in the future (regression testing).\r\n* Make sure your branch name is prefixed by `feature`, `bugfix` or `release`\r\n* Have you read Constellation's Code of Conduct? By filing an issue, you are\r\nexpected to comply with it, including treating everyone with respect:\r\nhttps://github.com/constellation-app/constellation/blob/master/CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md\r\n\r\n-->\r\n\r\n### Prerequisites\r\n\r\n- [ ] Reviewed the [checklist](CHECKLIST.md)\r\n\r\n- [ ] Reviewed feedback from the \"Sonar Cloud\" bot. Note that you have to wait\r\n    for the \"CI / Unit Tests\") to complete first. Failed Unit tests can be \r\n    debugged by adding the label \"verbose logging\" to the GitHub PR.\r\n\r\n### Description of the Change\r\nCompare Graph allows the user to pick from a list of graphs. It is possible for the user to either pick both graphs as the same graph, or pick two graphs wit the same name. Both cases will be confusing and the best course of action seems to be to warn the user of this.\r\n\r\nI suggest the following, throw an exception when the compared graphs have the same name. This will force the user to change the name of one of the graphs, which will reduce confusion of the results, but also hint to them that they may have accidentally selected the same graph to compare with itself.\r\n\r\nI decided against a \"WARNING\" level of notification as it did not hint to me that the comparison was not done. An \"ERROR\" level message seemed to be the best fit.\r\n\r\nBelow is an image of the error which appears when the names for compared graphs are the same.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/58677759/150879646-6bea35c4-82e0-4df7-8f61-a9fe4166e554.png)\r\n\r\n<!--\r\n\r\nWe must be able to understand the design of your change from this description.\r\nIf we can't get a good idea of what the code will be doing from the description\r\nhere, the pull request may be closed at the maintainers' discretion. Keep in\r\nmind that the maintainer reviewing this PR may not be familiar with or have\r\nworked with the code here recently, so please walk us through the concepts.\r\n\r\n-->\r\n\r\n### Alternate Designs\r\nN/A\r\n<!--\r\n\r\nExplain what other alternates were considered and why the proposed version was\r\nselected.\r\n\r\n-->\r\n\r\n### Why Should This Be In Core?\r\nUsability\r\n<!--\r\n\r\nExplain why this functionality should be in Constellation Core as opposed to a\r\ndifferent module suite.
